# GitHub Actions secrets — Crypto Pay (photospheremedia/Crypto-Pay)
#
# NEVER commit real values. Store values in GitHub → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions.
# Repo admins bootstrap with the scripts below; collaborators with admin access can re-run them.
#
# Check what's set (names only):
#   gh secret list -R photospheremedia/Crypto-Pay
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. GITHUB ACTIONS SECRETS (CI/CD only — not used at Netlify runtime)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Secret name              | Workflow              | Where to get the value
# -------------------------|-----------------------|------------------------------------------
# SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN    | supabase.yml          | https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens (sbp_...)
# SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF     | supabase.yml          | usbxwewohpsbjwiuazpf (PhotoSphere project)
# RESEND_API_KEY           | supabase.yml (opt.)   | https://resend.com/api-keys (re_...) — syncs Auth SMTP on deploy
# NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN       | netlify.yml           | https://app.netlify.com/user/applications#personal-access-tokens
# NETLIFY_SITE_ID          | netlify.yml           | Netlify → Site → General → Site ID (API ID)
# PORKBUN_API_KEY          | dns-netlify.yml       | Porkbun → Account → API Access (pk1_...)
# PORKBUN_SECRET_API_KEY   | dns-netlify.yml       | Porkbun → Account → API Access (sk1_...)
# NETLIFY_SITE_HOSTNAME    | dns-netlify.yml       | e.g. dazzling-pithivier-e119b1.netlify.app
#
# Bootstrap commands (repo admin, after gh auth login):
#   pnpm supabase:secrets     # SUPABASE_* + RESEND_API_KEY (from .env.supabase + .env.local)
#   pnpm netlify:secrets      # NETLIFY_* (from .env.netlify or netlify link)
#   pnpm porkbun:secrets      # PORKBUN_* + NETLIFY_SITE_HOSTNAME (from .env.porkbun)
#
# Currently expected minimum for CI:
#   SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN, SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF, NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN, NETLIFY_SITE_ID
# Recommended add:
#   RESEND_API_KEY (keeps Supabase Auth SMTP in sync on supabase.yml deploy)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. LOCAL GITIGNORED FILES (developers — copy from teammate or dashboards)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# File                     | Purpose
# -------------------------|--------------------------------------------------
# .env.supabase            | SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN, SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF (CLI + MCP)
# apps/portal/.env.local   | App runtime: Supabase keys, Resend, Stripe, Groq, etc.
# .env.netlify             | NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN (optional; for pnpm netlify:secrets)
# .env.porkbun             | PORKBUN_API_KEY, PORKBUN_SECRET_API_KEY, NETLIFY_SITE_HOSTNAME
#
# Start from templates:
#   cp .env.supabase.example .env.supabase
#   cp apps/portal/.env.example apps/portal/.env.local
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. NETLIFY SITE ENV (production runtime — NOT in GitHub Secrets)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Set via Netlify UI or: pnpm netlify:env-sync (imports from apps/portal/.env.local)
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_FUNCTIONS_URL
# SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://cryptopay.sale
# RESEND_API_KEY
# EMAIL_FROM
# EMAIL_REPLY_TO
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY
# TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY
# GROQ_API_KEY
#
# Full app env template: apps/portal/.env.example (Stripe, Skrill, delivery, etc.)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. SUPABASE EDGE FUNCTION SECRETS (dashboard / CLI — NOT in GitHub)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Sync from .env.local: pnpm resend:sync
#
# RESEND_API_KEY
# EMAIL_FROM
# EMAIL_REPLY_TO
# (+ auto-injected: SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, …)
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. NEW COLLABORATOR CHECKLIST
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. GitHub org/repo access (private repo)
# 2. Get apps/portal/.env.local from admin (1Password / secure share — never Slack)
# 3. pnpm supabase:connect  → .env.supabase for CLI/MCP
# 4. pnpm netlify:link      → link crypto-pay-portal site
# 5. Optional repo admin: pnpm supabase:secrets && pnpm netlify:secrets && pnpm porkbun:secrets
